From: Arrow R WASM fix <arrow@apache.org>
Subject: [PATCH] GH-XXXXX: [R] Disable threading paths on Emscripten/WASM

On Emscripten (webR), pthread_create is not supported and will fail with
"thread constructor failed: Not supported". This affects two code paths:

1. RunWithCapturedRIfPossible() submits work to the IO thread pool
   executor, which attempts to spawn a thread even when
   ARROW_ENABLE_THREADING=OFF (the IO pool is separate from the CPU pool).

2. RTasks constructs a ThreadedTaskGroup via GetCpuThreadPool() when
   use_threads=TRUE.

Fix both by:
- Making CanRunWithCapturedR() return false on __EMSCRIPTEN__, so all
  parquet/feather/CSV reads go through the synchronous path.
- Forcing arrow.use_threads=FALSE on Emscripten in .onLoad, so RTasks
  never attempts threaded execution.

This ensures read_parquet(as_data_frame=FALSE) correctly returns an
Arrow Table (instead of crashing) and eliminates the spurious thread
error on WASM.
---
 r/R/arrow-package.R             | 5 +++++
 r/src/safe-call-into-r-impl.cpp | 8 +++++++-
 2 files changed, 12 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/r/R/arrow-package.R b/r/R/arrow-package.R
index abcdef1..1234567 100644
--- a/r/R/arrow-package.R
+++ b/r/R/arrow-package.R
@@ -149,6 +149,11 @@
   # We can't do this at package build time because list_compute_functions()
   # needs the C++ library loaded
   create_binding_cache()
 
+  if (identical(R.version$os, "emscripten")) {
+    # Disable multithreading on WASM/Emscripten (no pthread support)
+    options(arrow.use_threads = FALSE)
+  }
+
   if (tolower(Sys.info()[["sysname"]]) == "windows") {
     # Disable multithreading on Windows
     # See https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ARROW-8379
diff --git a/r/src/safe-call-into-r-impl.cpp b/r/src/safe-call-into-r-impl.cpp
index abcdef2..1234568 100644
--- a/r/src/safe-call-into-r-impl.cpp
+++ b/r/src/safe-call-into-r-impl.cpp
@@ -46,7 +46,15 @@ bool SetEnableSignalStopSource(bool enabled) {
 }
 
 // [[arrow::export]]
-bool CanRunWithCapturedR() { return MainRThread::GetInstance().Executor() == nullptr; }
+bool CanRunWithCapturedR() {
+#ifdef __EMSCRIPTEN__
+  // Threading is not supported under Emscripten/WASM. Always take the
+  // synchronous path to avoid attempting pthread_create which will fail
+  // with "thread constructor failed: Not supported".
+  return false;
+#else
+  return MainRThread::GetInstance().Executor() == nullptr;
+#endif
+}
 
 // [[arrow::export]]
 std::string TestSafeCallIntoR(cpp11::function r_fun_that_returns_a_string,
